 frost, without warmth of feeling’, or perhaps ‘having the appearance of being covered with frost’ for one with white hair or a white beard. From Old English, Old High German, Old Norse <i>frost</i> ‘frost’."],"variants":[{"name":"Chell","meanings":["English (Staffordshire): from an unrecorded Middle English male or female personal name <i>Chell(e)</i> or <i>Chele</i>, Old English <i>Cēolla</i>, <i>Cēol</i>, or <i>Cēola</i>, short forms of names beginning with <i>Cēol-</i> ‘ship’, such as <i>Cēolbeorht</i> (male) and <i>Cēolflǣd</i> (female). Alternatively, perhaps a nickname from Middle English <i>chele</i>, <i>chile</i> (Old English <i>cīele</i>, <i>cēle</i>, <i>cȳle</i>) ‘cold, lacking sympathy’. Compare   Frost  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":10,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Thomas Frost I de Frostenden was born in 1372, in Frostenden, Suffolk, England, his father, Sir Walter De Frost Frostenden I, was 36 and his mother, Lady Alice, was 37. He married Margaret Legard about 1421, in Frostenden, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 8 August 1421, in Frostenden, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 49, and was buried in Frostenden, Suffolk, England."},"et":{"1372–8 August 1421":"1372–8. august 1421","1372–1421":"1372–1421","1374–Female":"1374–Surnud","1422–1489":"1422–1489","1337–1372":"1337–1372","1335–1375":"1335–1375","1337":"1337","1368":"1368","1335":"1335","1489":"1489","1422":"1422","1421":"1421","1375":"1375","1374":"1374","1372":"1372","about 1421":"umbes 1421","1382":"1382","8 August 1421":"8. august 1421","Frostenden, Suffolk, England":"Frostenden, Suffolk, England","Frostenden, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Frostenden, Suffolk, England",", , , England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1372–8 August 1421":"1372–8. elokuuta 1421","1372–1421":"1372–1421","1374–Female":"1374–Kuollut","1422–1489":"1422–1489","1337–1372":"1337–1372","1335–1375":"1335–1375","1337":"1337","1368":"1368","1335":"1335","1489":"1489","1422":"1422","1421":"1421","1375":"1375","1374":"1374","1372":"1372","about 1421":"noin 1421","1382":"1382","8 August 1421":"8. elokuuta 1421","Frostenden, Suffolk, England":"Frostenden, Suffolk, England","Frostenden, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Frostenden, Suffolk, England",", , , England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1372–8 August 1421":"1372–8 août 1421","1372–1421":"1372–1421","1374–Female":"1374–Décédée","1422–1489":"1422–1489","1337–1372":"1337–1372","1335–1375":"1335–1375","1337":"1337","1368":"1368","1335":"1335","1489":"1489","1422":"1422","1421":"1421","1375":"1375","1374":"1374","1372":"1372","about 1421":"environ 1421","1382":"1382","8 August 1421":"8 août 1421","Frostenden, Suffolk, England":"Frostenden, Suffolk, Angleterre","Frostenden, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Frostenden, Suffolk, Angleterre",", , , England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Sir Thomas Frost I de Frostenden est né en 1372, à Frostenden, Suffolk, Angleterre, s